<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>At CRM-perso,  we are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our CRM ticket and lead management application.</p>

<h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
<p>We collect personal and business information from you when you use our application. This may include:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Personal Information:</strong> Name, email address, and contact information.</li>
    <li><strong>Business Information:</strong> Details about your tickets, leads, customers, and other business-related data.</li>
    <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Information about how you interact with our application, such as login details, IP addresses, and actions within the application.</li>
</ul>

<h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
<p>Your information is used to provide and improve our CRM services, including:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Managing tickets and leads effectively.</li>
    <li>Providing customer support and responding to your inquiries.</li>
    <li>Improving the performance and features of our application.</li>
    <li>Sending you updates, promotions, and other relevant information (with your consent).</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Data Protection</h2>
<p>We take the security of your data seriously. We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your personal and business information from unauthorized access, disclosure, or misuse. However, please note that no system is entirely secure, and we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your data.</p>

<h2>4. Sharing Your Information</h2>
<p>We do not sell, rent, or share your personal or business information with third parties without your consent, except in the following circumstances:</p>
<ul>
    <li>To comply with legal obligations or respond to legal requests.</li>
    <li>To protect the safety, rights, or property of [Your Company Name], our users, or the public.</li>
    <li>To service providers who assist us in operating our application and providing our services (e.g., cloud storage providers).</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
<p>We retain your data for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy, unless a longer retention period is required by law or needed for legitimate business purposes.</p>

<h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
<p>You have the right to:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Access your personal data.</li>
    <li>Request corrections to inaccurate or incomplete information.</li>
    <li>Request deletion of your data (under certain conditions).</li>
    <li>Opt-out of receiving promotional communications from us.</li>
</ul>

<h2>7. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
<p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or legal obligations. Any updates will be posted on this page, and we will indicate the date of the most recent revision.</p>

<h2>8. Contact Us</h2>
<p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or how we handle your data, please contact us at:</p>
<p><strong>[Your Company Name]</strong><br>
Email: [Your email address]<br>
Phone: [Your phone number]</p>

